{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":553,"text":"OK, so today I want to talk\nabout how we talk about love."},{"time":5237,"text":"And specifically,"},{"time":6411,"text":"I want to talk about what's wrong\nwith how we talk about love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10673,"text":"Most of us will probably\nfall in love a few times"},{"time":14104,"text":"over the course of our lives,"},{"time":15593,"text":"and in the English language,\nthis metaphor, falling,"},{"time":19827,"text":"is really the main way that we\ntalk about that experience."},{"time":23592,"text":"I don't know about you,"},{"time":24767,"text":"but when I conceptualize this metaphor,"},{"time":26718,"text":"what I picture is straight\nout of a cartoon --"},{"time":30076,"text":"like there's a man,"},{"time":31396,"text":"he's walking down the sidewalk,"},{"time":33137,"text":"without realizing it, he crosses\nover an open manhole,"},{"time":36273,"text":"and he just plummets into the sewer below."},{"time":39958,"text":"And I picture it this way\nbecause falling is not jumping."},{"time":44769,"text":"Falling is accidental,"},{"time":46825,"text":"it's uncontrollable."},{"time":48751,"text":"It's something that happens to us\nwithout our consent."},{"time":52300,"text":"And this --"},{"time":53517,"text":"this is the main way we talk\nabout starting a new relationship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58336,"text":"I am a writer and I'm also\nan English teacher,"},{"time":62127,"text":"which means I think\nabout words for a living."},{"time":64436,"text":"You could say that I get paid\nto argue that the language we use matters,"},{"time":68610,"text":"and I would like to argue\nthat many of the metaphors we use"},{"time":72834,"text":"to talk about love --"},{"time":74425,"text":"maybe even most of them --"},{"time":76272,"text":"are a problem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":78700,"text":"So, in love, we fall."},{"time":81766,"text":"We're struck."},{"time":83255,"text":"We are crushed."},{"time":85331,"text":"We swoon."},{"time":87186,"text":"We burn with passion."},{"time":89738,"text":"Love makes us crazy,"},{"time":91739,"text":"and it makes us sick."},{"time":93796,"text":"Our hearts ache,"},{"time":95180,"text":"and then they break."},{"time":98226,"text":"So our metaphors equate\nthe experience of loving someone"},{"time":101394,"text":"to extreme violence or illness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104071,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":107101,"text":"They do."},{"time":108276,"text":"And they position us as the victims"},{"time":110283,"text":"of unforeseen and totally\nunavoidable circumstances."},{"time":114547,"text":"My favorite one of these is \"smitten,\""},{"time":117294,"text":"which is the past participle\nof the word \"smite.\""},{"time":120172,"text":"And if you look this word up\nin the dictionary --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":123264,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":124312,"text":"you will see that it can be defined\nas both \"grievous affliction,\""},{"time":128854,"text":"and, \"to be very much in love.\""},{"time":133716,"text":"I tend to associate the word \"smite\"\nwith a very particular context,"},{"time":137084,"text":"which is the Old Testament."},{"time":139560,"text":"In the Book of Exodus alone,\nthere are 16 references to smiting,"},{"time":144332,"text":"which is the word that the Bible uses\nfor the vengeance of an angry God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148129,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":149874,"text":"Here we are using the same word\nto talk about love"},{"time":152603,"text":"that we use to explain\na plague of locusts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155053,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":156105,"text":"Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":157385,"text":"So, how did this happen?"},{"time":159501,"text":"How have we come to associate love\nwith great pain and suffering?"},{"time":163516,"text":"And why do we talk about\nthis ostensibly good experience"},{"time":167529,"text":"as if we are victims?"},{"time":170556,"text":"These are difficult questions,"},{"time":172271,"text":"but I have some theories."},{"time":173941,"text":"And to think this through,"},{"time":175204,"text":"I want to focus on one\nmetaphor in particular,"},{"time":177856,"text":"which is the idea of love as madness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181088,"text":"When I first started\nresearching romantic love,"},{"time":183819,"text":"I found these madness\nmetaphors everywhere."},{"time":186604,"text":"The history of Western culture"},{"time":188731,"text":"is full of language that equates\nlove to mental illness."},{"time":193440,"text":"These are just a few examples."},{"time":195391,"text":"William Shakespeare:"},{"time":196758,"text":"\"Love is merely a madness,\""},{"time":198215,"text":"from \"As You Like It.\""},{"time":200092,"text":"Friedrich Nietzsche:"},{"time":201373,"text":"\"There is always some madness in love.\""},{"time":204559,"text":"\"Got me looking, got me looking\nso crazy in love -- \""}]},{"cues":[{"time":207449,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":209542,"text":"from the great philosopher,\nBeyonc√© Knowles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":212164,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":215083,"text":"I fell in love for the first\ntime when I was 20,"},{"time":217941,"text":"and it was a pretty turbulent\nrelationship right from the start."},{"time":221459,"text":"And it was long distance\nfor the first couple of years,"},{"time":224688,"text":"so for me that meant very high highs\nand very low lows."},{"time":229794,"text":"I can remember one moment in particular."},{"time":232580,"text":"I was sitting on a bed\nin a hostel in South America,"},{"time":235949,"text":"and I was watching the person\nI love walk out the door."},{"time":240151,"text":"And it was late,"},{"time":241788,"text":"it was nearly midnight,"},{"time":243072,"text":"we'd gotten into an argument over dinner,"},{"time":245073,"text":"and when we got back to our room,"},{"time":247046,"text":"he threw his things in the bag\nand stormed out."},{"time":251141,"text":"While I can no longer remember\nwhat that argument was about,"},{"time":254424,"text":"I very clearly remember\nhow I felt watching him leave."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259122,"text":"I was 22, it was my first time\nin the developing world,"},{"time":263424,"text":"and I was totally alone."},{"time":266412,"text":"I had another week until my flight home,"},{"time":269803,"text":"and I knew the name\nof the town that I was in,"},{"time":272195,"text":"and the name of the city\nthat I needed to get to to fly out,"},{"time":275802,"text":"but I had no idea how to get around."},{"time":279842,"text":"I had no guidebook and very little money,"},{"time":283043,"text":"and I spoke no Spanish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285547,"text":"Someone more adventurous than me"},{"time":287668,"text":"might have seen this as\na moment of opportunity,"},{"time":290122,"text":"but I just froze."},{"time":292406,"text":"I just sat there."},{"time":294738,"text":"And then I burst into tears."},{"time":297357,"text":"But despite my panic,"},{"time":299752,"text":"some small voice in my head thought,"},{"time":302346,"text":"\"Wow. That was dramatic."},{"time":304707,"text":"I must really be doing\nthis love thing right.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":307430,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":309242,"text":"Because some part of me\nwanted to feel miserable in love."},{"time":314226,"text":"And it sounds so strange\nto me now, but at 22,"},{"time":317690,"text":"I longed to have dramatic experiences,"},{"time":320859,"text":"and in that moment, I was irrational\nand furious and devastated,"},{"time":326081,"text":"and weirdly enough,"},{"time":327329,"text":"I thought that this somehow\nlegitimized the feelings I had"},{"time":330729,"text":"for the guy who had just left me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334163,"text":"I think on some level I wanted\nto feel a little bit crazy,"},{"time":338550,"text":"because I thought that\nthat was how loved worked."},{"time":343141,"text":"This really should not be surprising,"},{"time":344972,"text":"considering that according to Wikipedia,"},{"time":347450,"text":"there are eight films,"},{"time":349747,"text":"14 songs,"},{"time":351768,"text":"two albums and one novel\nwith the title \"Crazy Love.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":355837,"text":"About half an hour later,\nhe came back to our room."},{"time":358987,"text":"We made up."},{"time":360162,"text":"We spent another mostly\nhappy week traveling together."},{"time":363003,"text":"And then, when I got home,"},{"time":364459,"text":"I thought, \"That was so\nterrible and so great."},{"time":369989,"text":"This must be a real romance.\""},{"time":373006,"text":"I expected my first love\nto feel like madness,"},{"time":375730,"text":"and of course, it met\nthat expectation very well."},{"time":379941,"text":"But loving someone like that --"},{"time":381656,"text":"as if my entire well-being depended\non him loving me back --"},{"time":385775,"text":"was not very good for me"},{"time":387892,"text":"or for him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389850,"text":"But I suspect this experience of love\nis not that unusual."},{"time":394026,"text":"Most of us do feel a bit mad\nin the early stages of romantic love."},{"time":398815,"text":"In fact, there is research to confirm\nthat this is somewhat normal,"},{"time":403280,"text":"because, neurochemically speaking,"},{"time":405190,"text":"romantic love and mental illness\nare not that easily distinguished."},{"time":411046,"text":"This is true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412221,"text":"This study from 1999 used blood tests"},{"time":416804,"text":"to confirm that the serotonin\nlevels of the newly in love"},{"time":419922,"text":"very closely resembled\nthe serotonin levels"},{"time":422743,"text":"of people who had been diagnosed\nwith obsessive-compulsive disorder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426072,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":427104,"text":"Yes, and low levels of serotonin"},{"time":429825,"text":"are also associated\nwith seasonal affective disorder"},{"time":433451,"text":"and depression."},{"time":435687,"text":"So there is some evidence"},{"time":437971,"text":"that love is associated with changes\nto our moods and our behaviors."},{"time":442343,"text":"And there are other studies to confirm"},{"time":446374,"text":"that most relationships begin this way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450660,"text":"Researchers believe\nthat the low levels of serotonin"},{"time":454847,"text":"is correlated with obsessive thinking\nabout the object of love,"},{"time":458906,"text":"which is like this feeling that someone\nhas set up camp in your brain."},{"time":462988,"text":"And most of us feel this way\nwhen we first fall in love."},{"time":465943,"text":"But the good news is,\nit doesn't always last that long --"},{"time":469093,"text":"usually from a few months\nto a couple of years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":473352,"text":"When I got back from my trip\nto South America,"},{"time":476184,"text":"I spent a lot of time alone in my room,"},{"time":479785,"text":"checking my email,"},{"time":481149,"text":"desperate to hear from the guy I loved."},{"time":484545,"text":"I decided that if my friends could not\nunderstand my grievous affliction,"},{"time":489917,"text":"then I did not need their friendship."},{"time":491890,"text":"So I stopped hanging out\nwith most of them."},{"time":494387,"text":"And it was probably the most\nunhappy year of my life."},{"time":499086,"text":"But I think I felt like\nit was my job to be miserable,"},{"time":503849,"text":"because if I could be miserable,"},{"time":505665,"text":"then I would prove how much I loved him."},{"time":508356,"text":"And if I could prove it,"},{"time":510265,"text":"then we would have to end up\ntogether eventually."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514050,"text":"This is the real madness,"},{"time":516162,"text":"because there is no cosmic rule"},{"time":518581,"text":"that says that great suffering\nequals great reward,"},{"time":522478,"text":"but we talk about love as if this is true."}]},{"cues":[{"time":527463,"text":"Our experiences of love\nare both biological and cultural."},{"time":531774,"text":"Our biology tells us that love is good"},{"time":534257,"text":"by activating these reward\ncircuits in our brain,"},{"time":537435,"text":"and it tells us that love is painful\nwhen, after a fight or a breakup,"},{"time":542079,"text":"that neurochemical reward is withdrawn."},{"time":545155,"text":"And in fact -- and maybe\nyou've heard this --"},{"time":547621,"text":"neurochemically speaking,"},{"time":549489,"text":"going through a breakup is a lot\nlike going through cocaine withdrawal,"},{"time":553675,"text":"which I find reassuring."}]},{"cues":[{"time":555335,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":557066,"text":"And then our culture uses language"},{"time":559922,"text":"to shape and reinforce\nthese ideas about love."},{"time":562727,"text":"In this case, we're talking\nabout metaphors about pain"},{"time":565375,"text":"and addiction and madness."},{"time":567826,"text":"It's kind of an interesting feedback loop."},{"time":570294,"text":"Love is powerful and at times painful,"},{"time":573835,"text":"and we express this\nin our words and stories,"},{"time":577182,"text":"but then our words and stories prime us"},{"time":579704,"text":"to expect love to be powerful and painful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":583955,"text":"What's interesting to me\nis that all of this happens"},{"time":587152,"text":"in a culture that values\nlifelong monogamy."},{"time":590658,"text":"It seems like we want it both ways:"},{"time":592743,"text":"we want love to feel like madness,"},{"time":595718,"text":"and we want it to last an entire lifetime."},{"time":599561,"text":"That sounds terrible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601148,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":603853,"text":"To reconcile this,"},{"time":605473,"text":"we need to either change our culture\nor change our expectations."},{"time":611408,"text":"So, imagine if we were all\nless passive in love."},{"time":615642,"text":"If we were more assertive,\nmore open-minded, more generous"},{"time":619812,"text":"and instead of falling in love,"},{"time":623137,"text":"we stepped into love."},{"time":626223,"text":"I know that this is asking a lot,"},{"time":628176,"text":"but I'm not actually\nthe first person to suggest this."},{"time":633012,"text":"In their book, \"Metaphors We Live By,\""},{"time":635545,"text":"linguists Mark Johnson and George Lakoff\nsuggest a really interesting solution"},{"time":640683,"text":"to this dilemma,"},{"time":642491,"text":"which is to change our metaphors."},{"time":645795,"text":"They argue that metaphors really do shape\nthe way we experience the world,"},{"time":651071,"text":"and that they can even act\nas a guide for future actions,"},{"time":654593,"text":"like self-fulfilling prophecies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657489,"text":"Johnson and Lakoff suggest\na new metaphor for love:"},{"time":661977,"text":"love as a collaborative work of art."},{"time":664872,"text":"I really like this way\nof thinking about love."},{"time":669028,"text":"Linguists talk about metaphors\nas having entailments,"},{"time":672574,"text":"which is essentially a way of considering\nall the implications of,"},{"time":676394,"text":"or ideas contained\nwithin, a given metaphor."},{"time":679350,"text":"And Johnson and Lakoff\ntalk about everything"},{"time":682283,"text":"that collaborating\non a work of art entails:"},{"time":684976,"text":"effort, compromise,\npatience, shared goals."},{"time":689655,"text":"These ideas align nicely\nwith our cultural investment"},{"time":693509,"text":"in long-term romantic commitment,"},{"time":695606,"text":"but they also work well\nfor other kinds of relationships --"},{"time":700020,"text":"short-term, casual, polyamorous,\nnon-monogamous, asexual --"},{"time":705700,"text":"because this metaphor brings\nmuch more complex ideas"},{"time":709609,"text":"to the experience of loving someone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712670,"text":"So if love is a collaborative work of art,"},{"time":717088,"text":"then love is an aesthetic experience."},{"time":721524,"text":"Love is unpredictable,"},{"time":724153,"text":"love is creative,"},{"time":726898,"text":"love requires communication\nand discipline,"},{"time":731055,"text":"it is frustrating\nand emotionally demanding."},{"time":734677,"text":"And love involves both joy and pain."},{"time":738742,"text":"Ultimately, each experience\nof love is different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":743759,"text":"When I was younger,"},{"time":745410,"text":"it never occurred to me that I was allowed\nto demand more from love,"},{"time":750102,"text":"that I didn't have to just accept\nwhatever love offered."},{"time":754775,"text":"When 14-year-old Juliet first meets --"},{"time":758128,"text":"or, when 14-year-old Juliet\ncannot be with Romeo,"},{"time":762077,"text":"whom she has met four days ago,"},{"time":764738,"text":"she does not feel disappointed or angsty."},{"time":769022,"text":"Where is she?"},{"time":770403,"text":"She wants to die."},{"time":772236,"text":"Right?"},{"time":773411,"text":"And just as a refresher,\nat this point in the play,"},{"time":775904,"text":"act three of five,"},{"time":777236,"text":"Romeo is not dead."},{"time":779641,"text":"He's alive,"},{"time":781005,"text":"he's healthy,"},{"time":782417,"text":"he's just been banished from the city."},{"time":785853,"text":"I understand that 16th-century Verona\nis unlike contemporary North America,"},{"time":791878,"text":"and yet when I first read this play,"},{"time":794880,"text":"also at age 14,"},{"time":797297,"text":"Juliet's suffering made sense to me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":801295,"text":"Reframing love as something\nI get to create with someone I admire,"},{"time":806676,"text":"rather than something\nthat just happens to me"},{"time":809144,"text":"without my control or consent,"},{"time":811690,"text":"is empowering."},{"time":813779,"text":"It's still hard."},{"time":815421,"text":"Love still feels totally maddening\nand crushing some days,"},{"time":820977,"text":"and when I feel really frustrated,"},{"time":823116,"text":"I have to remind myself:"},{"time":824995,"text":"my job in this relationship\nis to talk to my partner"},{"time":828363,"text":"about what I want to make together."},{"time":831923,"text":"This isn't easy, either."},{"time":834756,"text":"But it's just so much better\nthan the alternative,"},{"time":838672,"text":"which is that thing\nthat feels like madness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842839,"text":"This version of love is not about winning\nor losing someone's affection."},{"time":848761,"text":"Instead, it requires\nthat you trust your partner"},{"time":852383,"text":"and talk about things\nwhen trusting feels difficult,"},{"time":855481,"text":"which sounds so simple,"},{"time":857951,"text":"but is actually a kind\nof revolutionary, radical act."},{"time":863062,"text":"This is because you get to stop\nthinking about yourself"},{"time":867230,"text":"and what you're gaining\nor losing in your relationship,"},{"time":870395,"text":"and you get to start thinking\nabout what you have to offer."},{"time":874811,"text":"This version of love\nallows us to say things like,"},{"time":878240,"text":"\"Hey, we're not very good collaborators.\nMaybe this isn't for us.\""},{"time":883733,"text":"Or, \"That relationship\nwas shorter than I had planned,"},{"time":887618,"text":"but it was still kind of beautiful.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":890836,"text":"The beautiful thing\nabout the collaborative work of art"},{"time":893650,"text":"is that it will not paint\nor draw or sculpt itself."},{"time":897098,"text":"This version of love allows us\nto decide what it looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901033,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902208,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}